-path option for path of the program
-lang option for language font
-stype option for source type
for example 
	language is Hindi then --lang hin
	for Malayalam --lang mal
	for Telugu --lang tel
	for Tamil --lang tam
        for kannada --lang kan
        for Panjabi --lang pan
        for Bengali --lang ben
        for Urdu --lang urd

-s option for source font
-t option for target font

To run:

perl run-convertor.pl --path=$PWD --lang= sourcelanguage -stype sourcelanguagetype(SSF/ssf or TEXT/text) -s wx -t utf <inputfile in wx >out for wx to UTF-8.

for example

perl run-convertor.pl --path=$PWD --lang=hin -stype text -s wx -t utf < test_data/hin/hin.wx >output.utf

